ReimportAsset: If the import is a reimport for a specific asset, set the asset to reimport here.
ReimportSourceIndex: If we are doing a reimport, set the source index here. Some assets have more then one source file that each contains part of the asset content.
bIsAutomated: Tell Interchange that import is automated and it shouldn't present a modal window.
bFollowRedirectors: Tell Interchange to follow redirectors when determining the location an asset will be imported.
OverridePipelines: Adding overrides tells Interchange to use the specific custom set of pipelines instead of letting the user or the system choose.
ImportLevel: Level to import into when doing a scene import.
DestinationName: Optional custom name for the import.
bReplaceExisting: Determies whether to overwrite existing assets.
OnAssetDone: Delegates used to track the imported objects. // This is called each time an asset is imported or reimported from the import call.
OnAssetsImportDone: This is called when all the assets were imported from the source data.
OnSceneObjectDone: This is called each time an object in the scene is imported or reimported from the import call.
OnSceneImportDone: This is called when all the scene objects were imported from the source data.
